    "date": "2018-01-24",
    "comment": "Rationale: Authors identified Prr7 in a proteomic study of the PSD fraction and developed a polyclonal antibody against it. They found that Prr7 is enriched in PSD fractions of the hippocampus and cerebral cortex. Purified Prr7 immunoprecipitated NR2B, NR1 and PSD-95 and pull-down assay shows direct interaction between Prr7 and PSD-95.. Experimental description: For PDS preparations used for the proteomic study forebrains of Wistar six-week-old rats were used.\n\n\"The PRR7 antibody was generated by immunizing rabbits with a synthetic peptide, PRPWSYPRQAESDMSK, corresponding to residues 129-144 in mouse and rat PRR7, and residues 134-149 in the human form, respectively.\"",
